rom wills, inventories and rolls of livery, sumptuary laws, moral and satirical works condemning contemporary fashions, an OldEnglish epic, and English and French romances. The texts themselves are in Old and Middle English, Latin and Anglo-Norman French, with some of the documents switching between more than one of these languages. They are presented with introduction, glossary and detailed notes. Louise M. Sylvester is Reader in English Language at the University of Westminster; Mark Chambers is a Post-Doctoral Research Associate at Durham University; Gale R. Owen-Crocker is Professor of Anglo-Saxon Culture at the University of Manchester.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aClothing and dressxHistoryyMedieval, 500-1500zGreat Britain. 0aTextile fabrics, MedievalzGreat Britain. 4aMedieval History. 4aMedieval Literature. 7aREFERENCE / General.2bisacsh  aCostume.  areenactment.1 aChambers, Mark C, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOwen-Crocker, Gale R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSylvester, Louise, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311143136940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782043836?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782043836423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782043836/original  a978-3-11-143136-9  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles